    {
      "type": "action",
      "tool": "read",
      "code": "{\"filePath\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\LLM-Test\\\\Documents\\\\agentsong\\\\README.md\"}",
      "output": "<path>C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Documents\\agentsong\\README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentSON\n2: \n3: **Agent + JSON** вҖ” Yet Another JSON, but metadata-rich and built for the agentic era.\n4: \n5: ## What's in a Name\n6: \n7: | Component | Meaning |\n8: |-----------|---------|\n9: | **Agent** | AI coding agents (Cursor, Claude Code, opencode, MiniMax, etc.) |\n10: | **SON** | JSON вҖ” the format it's built on |\n11: \n12: Like **JSON** itself вҖ” which was \"just another data format\" but became universal because it was simple, readable, and worked everywhere вҖ” **AgentSON** is \"just another JSON\" but designed specifically for the agentic era.\n13: \n14: **AgentSON = Agent + JSON**\n15: \n16: It's immediately recognizable (everyone knows JSON), signals the format (it IS JSON with a schema), and differentiates from \"yet another format\" to \"the JSON for agents.\"\n17: \n18: ## The Problem\n19: \n20: Every AI coding agent stores session data in its own proprietary SQLite database:\n21: \n22: | Tool | Database | Tables | Schema |\n23: |------|----------|--------|--------|\n24: | opencode | `opencode.db` | 21 | session, message, part, todo |\n25: | MiniMax | `sqlite.db` | 20 | sessions, session_messages |\n26: | Antigravity IDE | `*.db` | 7 | trajectory_meta, steps |\n27: | Chrome DevTools AI | Preferences JSON | вҖ” | user-query, thought, action |\n28: \n29: **Nobody has done for agent session logs what OpenAPI did for REST APIs.**\n30: \n31: ## The Solution\n32: \n33: AgentSON provides:\n34: \n35: 1. **A specification** вҖ” JSON Schema for agent session data\n36: 2. **Readers** вҖ” SQLite parsers for each tool's database\n37: 3. **A normalizer** вҖ” Converts tool-specific schemas to AgentSON format\n38: 4. **A CLI** вҖ” Export, search, and render sessions\n39: 5. **A VSCode extension** вҖ” Hydrate context across tools\n40: \n41: ## File Extension\n42: \n43: AgentSON files use the `.AgentSON` extension:\n44: \n45: ```\n46: my-session.AgentSON\n47: ```\n48: \n49: This makes them:\n50: - **Immediately identifiable** вҖ” not `.json` (too generic), not `.ailog` (old name)\n51: - **Grep-friendly** вҖ” `grep -r \"nightscout\" *.AgentSON`\n52: - **Tool-associated** вҖ” can be associated with the AgentSON CLI or viewer\n53: - **Windows-friendly** вҖ” `.agentson` (lowercase) also works on Windows\n54: \n55: ## Quick Start\n56: \n57: ```bash\n58: # List opencode sessions\n59: python cli/main.py list --tool opencode\n60: \n61: # Export a session\n62: python cli/main.py export --tool opencode --session ses_xxx --output ./sessions/\n63: \n64: # Export all sessions\n65: python cli/main.py export --tool opencode --all --output ./sessions/\n66: \n67: # Render as Markdown\n68: python cli/main.py render session.AgentSON --format md\n69: \n70: # Push to Supabase (optional)\n71: python cli/main.py push session.AgentSON\n72: \n73: # Pull from Supabase\n74: python cli/main.py pull --search \"nightscout\"\n75: ```\n76: \n77: ## Schema\n78: \n79: ```json\n80: {\n81:   \"$schema\": \"https://agentsong.dev/schema/v1.json\",\n82:   \"id\": \"session-2026-07-04-001\",\n83:   \"tool\": {\"name\": \"opencode\", \"session_id\": \"ses_xxx\"},\n84:   \"agent\": {\"name\": \"mimo-v2.5-free\", \"provider\": \"opencode\"},\n85:   \"entries\": [\n86:     {\"type\": \"user-query\", \"text\": \"...\"},\n87:     {\"type\": \"thought\", \"text\": \"...\"},\n88:     {\"type\": \"action\", \"tool\": \"bash\", \"code\": \"...\", \"output\": \"...\"},\n89:     {\"type\": \"answer\", \"text\": \"...\"},\n90:     {\"type\": \"side-effect\", \"action\": \"file_write\", \"path\": \"...\"}\n91:   ]\n92: }\n93: ```\n94: \n95: ## Entry Types\n96: \n97: | Type | Description |\n98: |------|-------------|\n99: | `user-query` | User's input or question |\n100: | `context` | Additional context (data used, DOM info) |\n101: | `querying` | Agent is processing |\n102: | `title` | Section or step title |\n103: | `thought` | Agent's reasoning/thinking |\n104: | `action` | Tool execution (code + output) |\n105: | `answer` | Agent's response |\n106: | `side-effect` | File changes, state mutations |\n107: \n108: ## Supported Tools\n109: \n110: | Tool | Status | Reader |\n111: |------|--------|--------|\n112: | opencode | вң… Working | `readers/opencode.py` |\n113: | MiniMax | вң… Working | `readers/minimax.py` |\n114: | Antigravity IDE | вң… Working | `readers/antigravity.py` |\n115: | Chrome DevTools AI | вҡ пёҸ Unknown storage | JS snippet (experimental) |\n116: | Cursor | рҹ”ң Planned | вҖ” |\n117: | Claude Code | рҹ”ң Planned | вҖ” |\n118: \n119: ### Chrome DevTools AI Status\n120: \n121: Chrome DevTools AI stores session data in an unknown location. The `ai_assistance: {}` field in Preferences JSON is empty, despite extensive usage visible in screenshots. The actual storage mechanism remains unclear вҖ” possibly cloud sync or different local storage.\n122: \n123: ## Use Cases\n124: \n125: ### For Individuals\n126: - Search your AI history: `grep -r \"smtpjs\" *.agentsong`\n127: - Resume sessions in different tools\n128: - Backup that survives tool changes\n129: - Personal training data for fine-tuning\n130: \n131: ### For Teams\n132: - Audit trail of AI-generated code\n133: - Onboarding: ship new devs your session archive\n134: - Knowledge persistence across team changes\n135: \n136: ### For Agent Builders\n137: - Standardized eval datasets\n138: - Real session traces for fine-tuning\n139: - Tool-use analysis across agents\n140: \n141: ## Architecture\n142: \n143: ### Two-Layer Design\n144: \n145: | Layer | What | Like |\n146: |-------|------|------|\n147: | **Open Spec** | `.agentsong` file format | Dev Containers вҖ” portable, file-based, works offline |\n148: | **Managed Instance** | Supabase backend | GitHub вҖ” sync, search, collaboration |\n149: \n150: ```\n151: Git (local, file-based) вҶ’ GitHub (cloud, collaboration)\n152: AgentSON (file-based) вҶ’ AgentSON Cloud (Supabase)\n153: ```\n154: \n155: ### The Flow\n156: \n157: ```\n158: в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\n159: в”Ӯ                    AgentSON Architecture                     в”Ӯ\n160: в”ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Ө\n161: в”Ӯ                                                             в”Ӯ\n162: в”Ӯ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ        в”Ӯ\n163: в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ   Cursor    в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ Claude Code в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ   opencode  в”Ӯ        в”Ӯ\n164: в”Ӯ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ        в”Ӯ\n165: в”Ӯ         в”Ӯ                в”Ӯ                в”Ӯ                  в”Ӯ\n166: в”Ӯ         в–ј                в–ј                в–ј                  в”Ӯ\n167: в”Ӯ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ   в”Ӯ\n168: в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ         .AgentSON Files (Open Spec)                  в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ\n169: в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ     Portable, vendor-neutral, file-based             в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ\n170: в”Ӯ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ   в”Ӯ\n171: в”Ӯ                             в”Ӯ                                в”Ӯ\n172: в”Ӯ              в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”јв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ               в”Ӯ\n173: в”Ӯ              в–ј              в–ј              в–ј               в”Ӯ\n174: в”Ӯ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ      в”Ӯ\n175: в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ   Local CLI  в”Ӯ в”Ӯ   Supabase   в”Ӯ в”Ӯ  Web Viewer  в”Ӯ      в”Ӯ\n176: в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  (offline)   в”Ӯ в”Ӯ  (optional)  в”Ӯ в”Ӯ   (shared)   в”Ӯ      в”Ӯ\n177: в”Ӯ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ      в”Ӯ\n178: в”Ӯ                                                             в”Ӯ\n179: в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n180: ```\n181: \n182: ## Repository Structure\n183: \n184: ```\n185: agentsong/\n186: в”ңв”Җв”Җ README.md              # This file\n187: в”ңв”Җв”Җ PRD.md                 # Full product requirements\n188: в”ңв”Җв”Җ PERSONAS-AND-USER-STORIES.md  # User personas and stories\n189: в”ңв”Җв”Җ spec/\n190: в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ v1.json            # JSON Schema\n191: в”ңв”Җв”Җ readers/               # Tool-specific readers\n192: в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ opencode.py        # вң… Working\n193: в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ minimax.py         # вң… Working\n194: в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ antigravity.py     # вң… Working\n195: в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ libre.py           # вң… Working (FreeStyle Libre 2)\n196: в”ңв”Җв”Җ normalizer/            # Schema conversion (planned)\n197: в”ңв”Җв”Җ renderers/             # Output formats (planned)\n198: в”ңв”Җв”Җ cli/                   # Command-line interface\n199: в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ main.py            # вң… Working\n200: в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ supabase_client.py # вң… Working\n201: в”ңв”Җв”Җ supabase/              # Managed instance schema\n202: в”ңв”Җв”Җ tests/                 # Test suite\n203: в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ test_opencode.py   # вң… Passing\n204: в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ test_minimax.py    # вң… Passing\n205: в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ test_antigravity.py # вң… Passing\n206: в”ңв”Җв”Җ examples/              # Example .agentsong files\n207: в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ opencode_example.AgentSON\n208: в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ minimax_example.AgentSON\n209: в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ antigravity_example.AgentSON\n210: в”ңв”Җв”Җ viewers/\n211: в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ web/index.html     # вң… Working (drag-and-drop viewer)\n212: в””в”Җв”Җ docs/\n213:     в””в”Җв”Җ sops/              # 14 Standard Operating Procedures\n214: ```\n215: \n216: ## Origin\n217: \n218: AgentSON evolved from `.ailog` вҖ” a format originally designed for Chrome DevTools AI session export. The schema was discovered in Chrome's Preferences JSON and generalized to cover all AI coding agents.\n219: \n220: The name \"AgentSON\" is a play on JSON вҖ” **Agent + JSON** вҖ” \"Yet Another JSON\" but metadata-rich and built for the agentic era.\n221: \n222: See [PRD.md](PRD.md) for the full product requirements document.\n223: \n224: ## License\n225: \n226: MIT\n227: \n228: ---\n229: \n230: *\"Nobody has done for agent session logs what OpenAPI did for REST APIs or what containers.dev did for dev environments.\"*\n\n(End of file - total 230 lines)\n</content>",
